des:
Megos Smart Home products help you control home appliances. You can simply ask Alexa to turn on or turn off your light bulbs
There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust your device name - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo.
After connecting Alexa to your Replace your App name products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "Megos Smart Home” app in the android or ios app market;
(2). Register one tuya account in our “Megos Smart Home” app;
(3). You need to have some Megos Smart Home devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our “Megos Smart Home” app and change the appropriate name for your devices which will be used in “Megos” skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android, ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "Replace your skill name" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of “Megos”, and you'll be navigated to App name login page;
(9). Input your Replace your App name account username and password, you'll be redirected to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished.
You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on the bedroom light.”
“Alexa, turn off the bedroom light.”
“Alexa, set the bedroom light to 50%.”
“Alexa, brighten the bedroom light to 50%.”
“Alexa, dim the bedroom light to 50%.”
"Alexa, set bedroom light to green."
"Alexa, set bedroom light to cool white."
